13:42.874 --> 13:45.809
- <font face="Rockwell">(RUMBLING SLOWS, BUZZER SOUNDING)</font>
- <font face="Rockwell">TIMOTHY:</font> My family.

13:45.811 --> 13:48.812
<font face="Rockwell">(RUMBLING STOPS, BUZZER
CONTINUES SOUNDING)</font>

13:48.814 --> 13:51.781
<font face="Rockwell">(PANTING)</font>

13:51.783 --> 13:54.358
This isn't happening. It's not...

13:54.361 --> 13:56.538
This isn't... It's not real.

13:56.541 --> 13:58.572
It's not. It's not. It's not.

13:58.575 --> 14:01.690
I think they're okay.
They're okay. They're okay.

14:01.693 --> 14:03.860
<font face="Rockwell">(TIMOTHY SOBBING)</font>

14:15.063 --> 14:17.763
<font face="Rockwell">MAN:</font> <i>We're taking you
to an outpost equipped</i>

14:17.769 --> 14:19.152
<i>for long-term habitation.</i>

14:19.155 --> 14:21.475
<font face="Rockwell">WOMAN:</font> It's one of ten around the world,

14:21.478 --> 14:23.847
each constructed in
minimal fallout zones.

14:23.849 --> 14:25.882
Are there other people there?

14:25.884 --> 14:28.952
Others like you, and those who
can afford to purchase a ticket.

14:28.954 --> 14:30.553
<font face="Rockwell">EMILY:</font> Rich people.

14:30.556 --> 14:32.561
- Of course.
- <font face="Rockwell">MAN:</font> The money they paid

14:32.564 --> 14:34.498
helped finance this operation.

14:40.665 --> 14:42.732
<font face="Rockwell">(VEHICLE SLOWS, STOPS)</font>

14:42.734 --> 14:44.717
Put these on.

14:57.616 --> 14:59.783
<font face="Rockwell">(GATES CLACK OPEN)</font>

15:07.893 --> 15:10.493
<font face="Rockwell">(TIMOTHY PANTING)</font>

15:10.495 --> 15:12.085
<font face="Rockwell">(EMILY PANTING)</font>

15:12.088 --> 15:14.112
<font face="Rockwell">(GATES CLACK)</font>

15:50.635 --> 15:52.819
<font face="Rockwell">(INDISTINCT, DISTANT CHATTER)</font>

15:52.822 --> 15:53.827
<font face="Rockwell">WOMAN:</font> Sorry.

15:53.830 --> 15:55.185
<font face="Rockwell">MAN:</font> Please. It wasn't her fault.

15:55.188 --> 15:57.506
<font face="Rockwell">WOMAN:</font> Please. We won't
do it again. We promise.

15:57.509 --> 15:58.908
<font face="Rockwell">MAN:</font> Please!

15:58.910 --> 16:00.358
<font face="Rockwell">(GUNSHOTS)</font>

16:00.361 --> 16:01.945
<font face="Rockwell">(TIMOTHY GASPING)</font>

16:01.947 --> 16:03.680
Oh, my God.

16:03.682 --> 16:04.914
<font face="Rockwell">(PANTING)</font>

16:08.520 --> 16:10.553
<font face="Rockwell">(TIMOTHY PANTS LOUDLY)</font>

16:19.798 --> 16:21.764
<font face="Rockwell">(TIMOTHY PANTING)</font>

16:31.943 --> 16:34.249
<font face="Rockwell">(TIMOTHY CONTINUES PANTING LOUDLY)</font>

16:34.252 --> 16:36.219
<font face="Rockwell">(BEEPS)</font>

16:39.518 --> 16:41.684
<font face="Rockwell">(DOOR CLACKS)</font>

16:44.756 --> 16:46.723
<font face="Rockwell">(TIMOTHY PANTING)</font>

16:55.934 --> 16:57.901
<font face="Rockwell">(DOORS CLACK OPEN)</font>

17:06.545 --> 17:08.478
<font face="Rockwell">(LOUD PANTING)</font>

17:10.773 --> 17:13.742
<font face="Rockwell">(DOORS CLACK, WHOOSH SHUT)</font>

17:15.921 --> 17:17.887
<font face="Rockwell">(MECHANICAL WHOOSHING)</font>

17:26.565 --> 17:28.491
<font face="Rockwell">(HISSES LOUDLY)</font>

17:33.991 --> 17:35.838
<font face="Rockwell">(HISSES LOUDLY)</font>

17:44.280 --> 17:46.616
<font face="Rockwell">(TIMOTHY PANTING)</font>

17:46.618 --> 17:48.685
<font face="Rockwell">(HISSES LOUDLY)</font>

17:54.826 --> 17:56.569
<font face="Rockwell">(HISSES LOUDLY)</font>

17:58.563 --> 18:00.530
<font face="Rockwell">(CLICK, BUZZER SOUNDS)</font>

18:04.311 --> 18:06.678
<font face="Rockwell">(CANE CLINKS AGAINST FLOOR)</font>

18:10.542 --> 18:13.643
<font face="Rockwell">(CLINKING CONTINUES)</font>

18:16.276 --> 18:18.476
<font face="Rockwell">(DOORS WHOOSH OPEN)</font>

18:25.924 --> 18:27.890
I am Wilhemina Venable.

18:29.028 --> 18:31.499
Welcome to Outpost Three.

18:40.928 --> 18:42.895
<font face="Rockwell">TIMOTHY:</font> This is a fallout shelter?

18:45.543 --> 18:47.194
It is now.

18:47.197 --> 18:51.499
For many years, it served
as an exclusive boys' school.

18:51.502 --> 18:55.504
<font face="Rockwell">EMILY:</font> What kind of boys'
school is subterranean?

18:55.507 --> 18:58.980
The Cooperative, to whom we
owe our eternal gratitude,

18:58.983 --> 19:00.823
took ownership and converted it

19:00.825 --> 19:02.659
once they realized what was coming.

19:02.661 --> 19:04.132
<font face="Rockwell">EMILY:</font> The end?

19:04.135 --> 19:06.960
No. The beginning.

19:08.432 --> 19:11.699
The Cooperative has plans
far beyond the temporary

19:11.702 --> 19:13.780
cleansing fire of the bomb.

19:13.783 --> 19:17.194
The Cooperative is not made
up of nations or armies.

19:17.197 --> 19:20.496
It's a collection of
the dozen greatest minds

19:20.499 --> 19:22.645
mankind has to offer.

19:24.323 --> 19:27.591
The visionaries.

19:27.594 --> 19:29.941
<font face="Rockwell">TIMOTHY:</font> They weren't visionary enough

19:29.944 --> 19:32.132
to think we might be able
to use some generators?

19:32.135 --> 19:35.152
It may be seem to you a
regression, Mr. Campbell,

19:35.155 --> 19:36.826
our way of life here,

19:36.828 --> 19:39.462
but you'd be dead wrong.

19:39.464 --> 19:42.799
Technology is what destroyed the world.

19:42.801 --> 19:46.550
Social media gave people
the illusion they were equal.

19:46.553 --> 19:50.540
Now that's all been swept away.

19:50.542 --> 19:53.509
The natural order will restore itself.

19:53.511 --> 19:56.116
I'll show you to your rooms.

19:56.119 --> 19:59.881
As Purples, you will each be
furnished with a private suite.

19:59.884 --> 20:01.835
<font face="Rockwell">EMILY:</font> What's a "Purple"?

20:09.118 --> 20:12.186
The elite.

20:12.189 --> 20:14.589
The worthy.

20:14.592 --> 20:17.426
Those chosen to survive.

20:24.506 --> 20:26.382
I'm supposed to wear this shit?

20:26.385 --> 20:28.530
In The Outpost, everyone
knows their place.

20:28.533 --> 20:30.600
The Purples wear purple,

20:30.603 --> 20:32.714
the Grays, gray.

20:32.717 --> 20:34.751
Who are the Grays?

20:34.753 --> 20:36.886
Grays are our worker ants.

20:36.888 --> 20:40.225
Still a necessary component

20:40.228 --> 20:43.262
of any functioning society.

20:44.427 --> 20:47.561
The Grays are here to serve.

20:47.564 --> 20:51.399
And grateful for the opportunity.

20:51.402 --> 20:54.903
The alternative being nuclear winter,

20:54.906 --> 20:57.840
cancer, death.

20:57.842 --> 20:59.875
So what are you?

20:59.878 --> 21:01.444
I am neither.

21:02.996 --> 21:06.225
Rather, I am the strong
right arm of The Cooperative.

21:08.228 --> 21:10.261
Think of me as their face.

21:15.123 --> 21:17.090
<font face="Rockwell">EMILY:</font> So you're not a Purple?

21:22.901 --> 21:25.735
The house rules are simple.

21:25.737 --> 21:29.906
You will refer to me
only as "Ms. Venable."

21:32.544 --> 21:34.577
You may never leave the building.

21:34.579 --> 21:37.272
If you wander

21:37.275 --> 21:39.808
out onto the grounds, you
will not be allowed back in

21:39.811 --> 21:43.586
due to the danger of
radiation contamination.

21:43.588 --> 21:45.588
You will take your chances

21:45.590 --> 21:48.499
with the canker pus
monsters beyond the gates.

21:57.756 --> 22:01.382
And no unauthorized
copulation of any kind,

22:01.385 --> 22:05.721
under any circumstances, no exceptions.

22:05.724 --> 22:08.600
What? You're joking.

22:08.603 --> 22:12.305
Ask the two Grays you saw
on the way in if it's a joke.

22:13.790 --> 22:17.186
You'll find the evening wear
on the left side of the armoire.

22:17.189 --> 22:19.289
We dress for dinner.

22:19.292 --> 22:22.835
Cocktails in the music
room at 6:30. Be prompt.

22:22.838 --> 22:26.944
There's no excuse for tardiness
when there's nothing else to do.

22:37.415 --> 22:39.382
<font face="Rockwell">(WATER RUNNING)</font>

22:52.857 --> 22:54.824
<font face="Rockwell">(SIGHS)</font>

23:05.554 --> 23:10.290
<font face="Rockwell">FEMALE VOICE:</font> <font face="Rockwell">(WHISPERING)</font>
<i>Beware... Timothy.</i>

23:18.524 --> 23:21.525
<font face="Rockwell">(♫ "CALLING OCCUPANTS OF INTERPLANETARY
CRAFT" BY THE CARPENTERS PLAYS ♫)</font>

23:21.528 --> 23:25.986
<font face="Rockwell"> <i>♫ In your mind you have capacities ♫</i> </font>

23:25.989 --> 23:28.567
<font face="Rockwell"> <i>♫ You know ♫</i> </font>

23:28.569 --> 23:31.436
<font face="Rockwell"> <i>♫ To telepath messages ♫</i> </font>

23:31.438 --> 23:34.415
<font face="Rockwell"> <i>♫ Through the vast unknown ♫</i> </font>

23:34.418 --> 23:36.665
<font face="Rockwell"> <i>♫ Please, close your eyes ♫</i> </font>

23:36.668 --> 23:38.543
<font face="Rockwell"> <i>♫ And concentrate ♫</i> </font>

23:38.545 --> 23:40.445
<font face="Rockwell"> <i>♫ With every thought you think ♫</i> </font>

23:43.517 --> 23:46.582
This song... The same one every night.

23:46.585 --> 23:48.386
- Oh, here we go.
- <font face="Rockwell"> <i>♫ We're about to sing... ♫</i> </font>

23:48.388 --> 23:49.754
Where is it even coming from?

23:49.756 --> 23:51.523
And why do we have to listen to it?

23:51.525 --> 23:53.082
What are we missing here?

23:53.085 --> 23:55.489
About 99% of the world's population.

23:55.492 --> 23:57.596
Would've been better
off dying with them.

23:57.598 --> 23:59.531
Speak for yourself, darling.

23:59.533 --> 24:01.954
Wouldn't have to drink
this, whatever this is.

24:01.957 --> 24:03.410
It's mineral water.

24:03.413 --> 24:04.752
You get a chance to talk to Venable?

24:04.754 --> 24:06.571
No, she creeps me out.

24:06.573 --> 24:08.573
It's not fair that they get
to be Purples and not me.

24:08.575 --> 24:10.626
Okay, he refused to touch my hair

24:10.629 --> 24:13.511
if he was a Gray, and
she's been to the Oscars,

24:13.513 --> 24:15.513
and was best friends with Natalie Wood,

24:15.515 --> 24:17.282
so fucking get some perspective.

24:17.284 --> 24:22.067
It just plays over and
over, 24 hours a day.

24:22.070 --> 24:24.356
It's like Satan's Spotify playlist.

24:24.359 --> 24:25.996
<font face="Rockwell">(ANDRE LAUGHS)</font>

24:25.999 --> 24:29.000
<font face="Rockwell"> <i>♫ Contact with you... ♫</i> </font>

24:30.530 --> 24:32.270
<font face="Rockwell">EVIE:</font> Oh.

24:32.273 --> 24:34.265
Well, well, well.

24:34.268 --> 24:35.720
New blood.

24:35.723 --> 24:38.700
Come in. Don't be shy.

24:38.703 --> 24:40.605
You're Dinah Stevens.

24:40.607 --> 24:42.374
My mother used to watch your show.

24:42.376 --> 24:44.947
She said you beat the
pants off Oprah any day.

24:44.950 --> 24:46.957
Bless her heart... A million of her

24:46.960 --> 24:49.512
and I wouldn't have been
replaced by that telenovela.

24:51.318 --> 24:54.176
Um, what's happening out there?

24:54.179 --> 24:56.288
<font face="Rockwell"> <i>♫ We beseech you ♫</i> </font>

24:56.290 --> 24:58.673
- It's all gone.
- Everything.

24:58.676 --> 25:00.876
<font face="Rockwell"> <i>♫ Our Earth may never survive ♫</i> </font>

25:00.879 --> 25:03.461
<font face="Rockwell"> <i>♫ So do come, we beg you ♫</i> </font>

25:03.463 --> 25:06.822
<font face="Rockwell"> <i>♫ Please, interstellar policeman ♫</i> </font>

25:06.825 --> 25:08.489
<font face="Rockwell">(BELL RINGS)</font>

25:08.492 --> 25:10.125
<font face="Rockwell"> <i>♫ Oh, won't you give us a sign ♫</i> </font>

25:10.128 --> 25:12.061
<font face="Rockwell"> <i>♫ Give us a sign... ♫</i> </font>

25:12.064 --> 25:14.309
Dinner is served.

25:18.478 --> 25:20.445
<font face="Rockwell">(DISHES CLINKING)</font>

25:28.771 --> 25:30.035
It's all we get.

25:30.038 --> 25:31.905
Don't be too disappointed.

25:31.908 --> 25:33.993
Darling, you don't know
what disappointment is

25:33.996 --> 25:36.294
- until you've slept with Yul Brynner.
- <font face="Rockwell">(DINAH LAUGHS)</font>

25:36.296 --> 25:37.325
I want to die.

25:37.328 --> 25:41.059
The cube on your plate contains
every vitamin our body needs...

25:42.409 --> 25:44.075
...or so they tell us.

25:44.078 --> 25:46.403
<font face="Rockwell">COCO:</font> I'm still hungry.

25:46.406 --> 25:49.374
I am so tired of the hunger.

25:51.091 --> 25:54.226
Fuck this bullshit!

25:54.229 --> 25:56.448
With all the thought
that went into this place,

25:56.450 --> 25:59.892
they don't have a single bag
of Pirate's Booty in the pantry?

25:59.895 --> 26:02.970
For a hundred million dollars a ticket,

26:02.973 --> 26:04.790
I expect goddamn Gordon Ramsay

26:04.793 --> 26:08.075
in the kitchen cooking us real food!

26:08.078 --> 26:10.233
<font face="Rockwell">(CANE TAPS FLOOR)</font>

26:16.403 --> 26:18.203
<font face="Rockwell">TIMOTHY:</font> Oh.

26:24.678 --> 26:26.678
I'm going to be very clear

26:26.680 --> 26:29.481
so there will be no misunderstanding.

26:29.483 --> 26:32.717
We have enough nutrition
for the next 18 months.

26:32.719 --> 26:34.619
And if our situation doesn't improve,

26:34.621 --> 26:36.488
you can count on less and less.

26:39.493 --> 26:42.327
Situation? What is our situation?

26:45.665 --> 26:48.266
We had a perimeter alert this morning.

26:49.216 --> 26:52.103
Something penetrated the grounds.

26:52.106 --> 26:53.571
<font face="Rockwell">(BIRD WINGS FLAPPING)</font>

26:56.943 --> 26:59.411
<font face="Rockwell">MEAD:</font> Ah, God.

26:59.413 --> 27:02.514
- Ah, shit.
- <font face="Rockwell">(BIRD COOS)</font>

27:05.619 --> 27:07.177
<font face="Rockwell">VENABLE:</font> <i>It was a carrier pigeon,</i>

27:07.180 --> 27:09.651
<i>delivering a message
from our benefactors.</i>

27:09.654 --> 27:10.948
<font face="Rockwell">COCO:</font> <i>Wait. A pigeon?</i>

27:10.951 --> 27:12.223
<i>Can we eat it?</i>

27:14.287 --> 27:16.694
It was contaminated by the fallout.

27:16.696 --> 27:18.296
Can we boil it?

27:18.298 --> 27:21.599
"There are no more governments.

27:21.601 --> 27:24.068
Only rotting mounds of corpses,

27:24.071 --> 27:26.029
too many to bury.

27:26.032 --> 27:28.672
Starving people kill
for a piece of bread.

27:28.675 --> 27:31.342
Three outposts have been overrun.

27:31.344 --> 27:33.445
We are the last vestiges

27:33.447 --> 27:36.514
of civilized life on the planet.

27:38.518 --> 27:41.013
Be vigilant."

27:41.016 --> 27:42.552
Everything we know is gone.

27:42.555 --> 27:44.170
In two weeks?

27:44.173 --> 27:46.106
That's all it took?

27:46.109 --> 27:47.691
<font face="Rockwell">MEAD:</font> It was always fragile.

27:47.694 --> 27:50.185
They made you think
the system was a rock.

27:50.188 --> 27:51.663
It was a water balloon.

27:51.665 --> 27:53.598
One prick of the needle and...
<font face="Rockwell">(POPS LIPS)</font>

27:53.600 --> 27:54.732
...that's all it took.

27:54.734 --> 27:56.667
<font face="Rockwell">VENABLE:</font> We will only survive

27:56.670 --> 27:58.670
if we follow the rules.

28:00.340 --> 28:01.739
<font face="Rockwell">(WHISPERING INDISTINCTLY)</font>

28:01.741 --> 28:03.541
There's a problem.

28:03.543 --> 28:05.162
We've detected a spike

28:05.165 --> 28:07.588
in the background radiation,
centered in this room.

28:07.591 --> 28:10.248
It's them; they just
came from the outside.

28:10.250 --> 28:12.383
No, no. We were checked when
we got here. We're clean!

28:12.385 --> 28:14.012
<font face="Rockwell">TIMOTHY:</font> No, we went
through decontamination.

28:14.014 --> 28:15.280
We were cleared.

28:15.283 --> 28:17.091
Place your hands on the table.

28:17.094 --> 28:18.355
And don't move.

28:18.358 --> 28:20.658
<font face="Rockwell">(GEIGER COUNTER CLICKING)</font>

28:22.591 --> 28:26.631
Radioactive contamination

28:26.633 --> 28:30.235
is a grave risk to our entire community.

28:30.237 --> 28:34.472
The clean rule is there
to protect all of us.

28:34.474 --> 28:37.003
A single stray gamma particle

28:37.006 --> 28:39.521
can cause skin lesions.

28:39.524 --> 28:42.546
Your DNA breaks apart,
your body disintegrates.

28:42.549 --> 28:45.550
You'll wish you died in the blast.

28:45.552 --> 28:49.687
But someone here decided

28:49.689 --> 28:53.084
that their individual
needs were more important.

28:53.087 --> 28:54.659
Someone went outside.

28:54.661 --> 28:56.427
Touched something dirty.

28:56.429 --> 28:58.329
<font face="Rockwell">(GEIGER COUNTER CONTINUES CLICKING)</font>

28:58.331 --> 29:00.029
It makes me sick to think this person

29:00.032 --> 29:04.567
was selfish enough to
risk contaminating all...

29:04.570 --> 29:07.371
<font face="Rockwell">MR. GALLANT:</font> No. No, no,
no no, no. That's a mistake,

29:07.374 --> 29:09.667
because the only thing
I've touched is Coco's hair.

29:09.670 --> 29:12.443
<font face="Rockwell">MEAD:</font> She's clean. You're dirty.

29:12.445 --> 29:13.611
No. This is impossible!

29:13.613 --> 29:15.490
That machine is wrong. Ow! <font face="Rockwell">(GROANS)</font>

29:15.493 --> 29:17.761
- <font face="Rockwell">EVIE:</font> This is outrageous. Stop! Please stop.
- <font face="Rockwell">(OTHERS EXCLAIMING)</font>

29:17.763 --> 29:19.417
- Bring him back!
- <font face="Rockwell">MR. GALLANT:</font> Evie!

29:19.419 --> 29:21.352
<font face="Rockwell">(GEIGER COUNTER CLICKING)</font>

29:26.814 --> 29:28.659
- No way. No. No way.
- No!

29:28.662 --> 29:31.068
- Get your hands off me!
- No! <font face="Rockwell">(SOBBING)</font>

29:31.071 --> 29:32.297
Take them

29:32.300 --> 29:34.979
- to the decontamination room.
- <font face="Rockwell">ANDRE:</font> No...

29:34.982 --> 29:37.569
<font face="Rockwell">(MR. GALLANT AND STU MOANING)</font>

29:37.571 --> 29:41.306
<font face="Rockwell">(MOANING, WAILING)</font>

29:43.610 --> 29:45.577
<font face="Rockwell">(CRYING, GROANING)</font>

29:47.302 --> 29:48.580
<font face="Rockwell">MR. GALLANT:</font> <font face="Rockwell">(MOANING)</font> No.

29:48.582 --> 29:51.215
<font face="Rockwell">(BOTH SCREAMING, CRYING)</font>

29:59.359 --> 30:01.459
<font face="Rockwell">(BOTH PANTING)</font>

30:01.461 --> 30:03.428
<font face="Rockwell">(GEIGER COUNTER CLICKING)</font>

30:04.464 --> 30:05.597
<font face="Rockwell">MR. GALLANT:</font> Oh, no.

30:14.708 --> 30:17.408
<font face="Rockwell">(WHIMPERS)</font>

30:17.410 --> 30:18.476
Clean.

30:18.478 --> 30:20.445
<font face="Rockwell">(CRYING)</font>

30:28.488 --> 30:31.556
<font face="Rockwell">(GEIGER COUNTER CLICKING RAPIDLY)</font>

30:31.558 --> 30:33.458
Dirty.

30:33.460 --> 30:35.021
<font face="Rockwell">STU:</font> Please, please. No.

30:35.024 --> 30:36.920
I can't go through that spray again.

30:37.866 --> 30:39.599
You won't have to.

30:40.323 --> 30:42.357
<font face="Rockwell">(SCREAMS)</font>

31:07.433 --> 31:09.367
<font face="Rockwell">(KNOCKING ON DOOR)</font>

31:11.591 --> 31:12.724
Yes?

31:12.726 --> 31:14.996
It's me. Are you decent?

31:23.334 --> 31:24.600
Never more so.

31:28.512 --> 31:29.988
Well?

31:34.614 --> 31:36.681
Ravishing might be too strong a word,

31:36.683 --> 31:38.716
but this one certainly becomes you.

31:38.718 --> 31:39.817
Don't you agree?

31:41.655 --> 31:43.451
If anyone sees us...

31:48.370 --> 31:50.670
We're the only ones who matter.

32:05.745 --> 32:07.712
<font face="Rockwell">(LAUGHS QUIETLY)</font>

32:09.924 --> 32:11.683
<font face="Rockwell">VENABLE:</font> How did you manage it?

32:11.685 --> 32:13.618
Stu and the Geiger counter?

32:13.620 --> 32:14.786
<font face="Rockwell">MEAD:</font> Easy.

32:14.788 --> 32:16.721
Set the sensitivity to ten,

32:16.723 --> 32:18.790
you can make anyone
sound like Chernobyl.

32:18.792 --> 32:21.626
It was lovely work.

32:21.628 --> 32:24.862
And a pleasure.

32:24.865 --> 32:27.733
It's strangely satisfying, isn't it?

32:30.300 --> 32:31.995
Dispensing punishment?

32:33.640 --> 32:36.643
I love their faces...

32:36.646 --> 32:40.796
that stupid "can't believe
this is happening to me"

32:40.799 --> 32:42.413
look they get.

32:42.415 --> 32:45.783
I'm not embarrassed to
say, it gives me a tingle.

32:50.840 --> 32:52.807
<font face="Rockwell">(LAUGHS)</font>

32:57.864 --> 33:01.566
I wonder what The Cooperative
would say about all of this,

33:01.568 --> 33:05.031
making up our own rules,
terrorizing the guests.

33:05.034 --> 33:07.117
You're still uncomfortable with this

33:07.120 --> 33:09.474
and that gives me pause.

33:09.476 --> 33:10.952
I'm military.

33:10.955 --> 33:13.929
My dad killed so many
Viet-Cong he lost count.

33:13.932 --> 33:18.483
Killing is in my DNA.

33:18.485 --> 33:22.198
But I still respect
the chain of command.

33:22.201 --> 33:25.723
The Cooperative's paid my
bills for a lot of years.

33:27.826 --> 33:32.462
Just hard for me to pretend
they're not my boss anymore.

33:32.465 --> 33:34.665
Forget The Cooperative.

33:36.503 --> 33:38.736
It's only us.

33:41.474 --> 33:43.541
<font face="Rockwell">ANDRE:</font> How could he be contaminated?

33:43.543 --> 33:46.844
Stu never went outside. He
was with me most of the time.

33:46.846 --> 33:50.715
Well, people do strange things
when they're stuck inside 24/7.

33:50.717 --> 33:53.343
- I've started masturbating with my off hand.
- <font face="Rockwell">(LAUGHING)</font>

33:53.346 --> 33:55.720
Are you saying he deserved this?

33:55.722 --> 33:57.874
I'm saying Stu was boring,

33:57.877 --> 33:59.416
and using up our food,

33:59.419 --> 34:01.691
and that lesions won't
work with my complexion.

34:01.694 --> 34:03.299
Fuck you!

34:03.302 --> 34:05.236
I hope they come for you next.

34:05.239 --> 34:07.338
Nobody's coming for anyone.

34:07.341 --> 34:09.341
Not unless you break the rules.

34:09.344 --> 34:11.536
This is a difficult time for everyone.

34:11.538 --> 34:15.339
As a small consolation,
we have a special treat.

34:19.712 --> 34:21.679
No cubes tonight?

34:23.315 --> 34:25.650
Enjoy the <i>bonne bouche.</i>

34:25.652 --> 34:27.916
Don't get used to it.

34:34.362 --> 34:36.338
You think bribing us with a hot meal's

34:36.341 --> 34:38.436
just gonna make everything okay?

34:39.732 --> 34:41.399
<font face="Rockwell">COCO:</font> Oh, my God.

34:41.400 --> 34:43.487
I think my mouth had an orgasm.

34:43.489 --> 34:47.737
Andre, we're not trying to bribe anyone,

34:47.739 --> 34:50.565
but there is something
we all need to understand.

34:50.568 --> 34:54.018
There is no "us" and "them."
We are in this together.

34:54.021 --> 34:56.257
No individual is greater than the group.

34:56.260 --> 34:57.843
We did what we had to do.

34:57.846 --> 34:59.937
This is quite simply a tragedy.

34:59.940 --> 35:03.421
Where have you been hiding the fresh meat?

35:03.423 --> 35:07.406
We have resources...
for special occasions.

35:07.409 --> 35:11.496
I've never tasted anything like it.

35:11.498 --> 35:12.867
It's chicken.

35:12.870 --> 35:14.699
That's not a chicken bone.

35:21.708 --> 35:24.475
<font face="Rockwell">(GASPS)</font>

35:24.477 --> 35:27.432
Tell me this doesn't look like a finger.

35:28.581 --> 35:30.414
<font face="Rockwell">(ANDRE GASPS)</font>

35:30.416 --> 35:32.252
Oh, Jesus Christ.

35:32.255 --> 35:36.090
Oh, this stew is Stu!

35:36.093 --> 35:39.218
Mallory, come here and stick
your finger down my throat!

35:39.221 --> 35:40.590
<font face="Rockwell">(ANDRE YELLING)</font>

35:40.593 --> 35:42.031
<font face="Rockwell">(GAGGING, COUGHING)</font>

35:42.034 --> 35:45.429
For heavens sakes, don't be ridiculous.

35:45.431 --> 35:48.533
There are lines that
can never be crossed.

35:48.535 --> 35:51.402
Not eating people is of the first rank.

35:51.404 --> 35:53.504
I don't care what it is.

35:53.506 --> 35:55.506
It's absolutely divine.

35:55.508 --> 35:57.318
And it's full of fiber.

35:57.321 --> 35:59.321
I'm going to finish every drop.

36:09.357 --> 36:15.310
<font face="Rockwell"> <i>♫ Calling occupants of
interplanetary craft ♫</i> </font>

36:15.313 --> 36:18.713
<font face="Rockwell"> <i>♫ Calling occupants ♫</i> </font>

36:18.716 --> 36:23.541
<font face="Rockwell"> <i>♫ Of interplanetary, most
extraordinary craft... ♫</i> </font>

36:25.435 --> 36:27.704
You're a monster.

36:27.706 --> 36:30.536
How could you keep eating?
You knew what it was.

36:31.476 --> 36:33.510
It was chicken, Andre.

36:33.512 --> 36:36.446
Delicious white-meat chicken.

36:36.448 --> 36:38.548
You're a cannibal.

36:38.550 --> 36:41.618
- <font face="Rockwell">(CRYING)</font> You're all cannibals!
- Think about it.

36:41.620 --> 36:43.720
- <font face="Rockwell">(ANDRE SOBS)</font>
- <font face="Rockwell">DINAH:</font> She ate it, too.

36:43.722 --> 36:45.488
Stu was contaminated.

36:45.490 --> 36:48.572
Why would Venable eat irradiated meat?

36:48.575 --> 36:49.776
<font face="Rockwell">TIMOTHY:</font> That's right.

36:49.779 --> 36:51.130
Why would she feed us poison?

36:51.133 --> 36:53.562
The whole reason she is
here is to keep us alive.

36:53.565 --> 36:55.665
But where's his body, then?

36:55.667 --> 36:58.724
I want to see it. I want to see Stu!

36:58.727 --> 37:01.904
Shut up! Shut up!

37:01.907 --> 37:04.185
Just listen.

37:05.644 --> 37:07.577
- I don't hear anything.
- <font face="Rockwell">EMILY:</font> Exactly.

37:07.579 --> 37:09.446
- The song stopped.
- <font face="Rockwell">(CLACKS)</font>

37:09.448 --> 37:13.650
<font face="Rockwell">(♫ INTRO TO MAUREEN MCGOVERN'S
"THE MORNING AFTER" PLAYS ♫)</font>

37:13.652 --> 37:16.453
It's been the same song
for two straight weeks.

37:16.456 --> 37:17.994
Why would they suddenly change it?

37:17.997 --> 37:21.232
<font face="Rockwell"> <i>♫ A morning after ♫</i> </font>

37:21.235 --> 37:23.725
- <font face="Rockwell"> <i>♫ If we can hold on ♫</i> </font>
- <font face="Rockwell">(♫ SINGING ALONG ♫)</font> <font face="Rockwell"> <i>♫ Hold on ♫</i> </font>

37:23.728 --> 37:27.307
- <font face="Rockwell"> <i>♫ Through the night ♫</i> </font>
- <font face="Rockwell"> <i>♫ Through the night ♫</i> </font>

37:27.310 --> 37:28.466
<font face="Rockwell"> <i>♫ We have a chance... ♫</i> </font>

37:28.469 --> 37:30.532
Don't you get it?! It's a message!

37:30.535 --> 37:32.802
Aah!

37:32.804 --> 37:39.575
<font face="Rockwell"> <i>♫ Let's keep on looking for the light ♫</i> </font>

37:39.578 --> 37:41.678
The Cooperative is trying
to tell us something!

37:41.680 --> 37:43.880
They're saying, "Hang
on. We're coming for you."

37:43.882 --> 37:46.041
- We're gonna be rescued.
- <font face="Rockwell">ANDRE:</font> Oh.

37:46.044 --> 37:48.341
Yes, The Cooperative is coming for us.

37:48.344 --> 37:50.520
Halle-fucking-lujah!

37:50.529 --> 37:53.585
- Mallory...
- <font face="Rockwell">(LAUGHTER, SHRIEKING)</font>

37:55.804 --> 37:58.595
<font face="Rockwell">(♫ INTRO TO MAUREEN MCGOVERN'S
"THE MORNING AFTER" PLAYS ♫)</font>

37:58.597 --> 38:05.088
<font face="Rockwell"> <i>♫ There's got to be a morning after ♫</i> </font>

38:05.091 --> 38:06.776
<font face="Rockwell"> <i>♫ If we can hold on... ♫</i> </font>

38:06.779 --> 38:08.979
Maybe it's time to eat somebody.

38:08.982 --> 38:11.674
Or just, like, an arm.

38:11.676 --> 38:14.088
<font face="Rockwell">TIMOTHY:</font> <i>He was right about the song.</i>

38:14.091 --> 38:16.263
<i>There</i> was <i> a morning after.</i>

38:16.266 --> 38:19.582
<i>It just looked exactly
like the previous morning.</i>

38:19.584 --> 38:22.916
<i>We weren't rescued,
and no one ever came.</i>

38:22.919 --> 38:26.010
<i>But nuclear winter came,</i>

38:26.013 --> 38:29.779
<i>and it finished off anything
the bombs had left alive.</i>

38:29.782 --> 38:31.815
<font face="Rockwell"> <i>♫ It's waiting right outside the storm... ♫</i> </font>

38:31.818 --> 38:34.158
<font face="Rockwell">TIMOTHY:</font> <i>The world got colder,</i>

38:34.161 --> 38:36.127
<i>deadlier.</i>

38:36.130 --> 38:39.536
<font face="Rockwell"> <i>♫ Why don't we cross
the bridge together... ♫</i> </font>

38:39.538 --> 38:42.872
<font face="Rockwell">TIMOTHY:</font> <i>But even in all of this death,</i>

38:42.874 --> 38:46.509
<i>something was born.</i>

38:46.511 --> 38:48.678
<i>Like everything in this place,</i>

38:48.680 --> 38:54.617
<i>we had to ration one kiss
per week, just to be safe.</i>

38:54.619 --> 38:57.251
<i>And though we couldn't be together</i>

38:57.254 --> 39:01.286
<i>in every way that we wanted,</i>

39:01.289 --> 39:05.728
<i>it was enough to keep
us from dying inside,</i>

39:05.730 --> 39:08.498
<i>like everyone else around us.</i>

39:08.500 --> 39:11.768
<font face="Rockwell">(ECHOING)</font> <font face="Rockwell"> <i>♫ In time... ♫</i> </font>

39:22.371 --> 39:24.137
<font face="Rockwell">(DOOR OPENS)</font>

39:24.140 --> 39:26.140
I have an announcement.

39:27.552 --> 39:29.552
This will be our last breakfast.

39:29.554 --> 39:32.382
We're cutting back to one meal a day.

39:32.385 --> 39:33.845
You can't be serious.

39:33.848 --> 39:36.587
An effective dieting technique.

39:36.590 --> 39:38.294
Yeah, so is starving to death!

39:38.297 --> 39:40.364
How are we supposed to
survive on half a cube?

39:40.367 --> 39:43.832
It's not optimal, but
also not impossible.

39:43.835 --> 39:46.647
Either way, we have no choice.

39:46.650 --> 39:48.850
Not if we want to keep eating at all.

39:50.779 --> 39:52.732
I fucking can't do this anymore!

39:52.735 --> 39:54.104
<font face="Rockwell">DINAH:</font> We don't know

39:54.107 --> 39:57.604
how strong we are until
we have to face adversity.

39:57.607 --> 40:00.167
This could be an opportunity
for all of us to grow.

40:00.170 --> 40:02.223
Finish that bumper sticker shit
you used to say on your show,

40:02.225 --> 40:04.387
and I'm strong enough to
shove this fork in your neck!

40:04.389 --> 40:05.365
<font face="Rockwell">EVIE:</font> Oh, calm down.

40:05.368 --> 40:07.115
<font face="Rockwell">COCO:</font> What is the point

40:07.118 --> 40:09.365
of all of this? Starving,

40:09.368 --> 40:11.426
killing each other, getting shot?

40:11.429 --> 40:14.024
All we're doing is waiting
around to find out how we die.

40:14.027 --> 40:15.507
I say we take our chances outside.

40:15.510 --> 40:17.784
She's right. We have to get out of here.

40:17.787 --> 40:19.702
Nobody's going anywhere.

40:22.443 --> 40:23.807
<font face="Rockwell">(DISH CLINKING)</font>

40:23.810 --> 40:25.042
What are you gonna do?!

40:25.045 --> 40:27.477
Shoot us all? Huh?!

40:27.479 --> 40:28.756
What are you gonna do?

40:28.759 --> 40:31.647
<font face="Rockwell">(ALARM BLARING)</font>

40:31.650 --> 40:35.107
Perimeter alert. There's been a breach.

40:40.854 --> 40:42.820
<font face="Rockwell">(DOORS CLACK OPEN)</font>

40:48.733 --> 40:50.700
<font face="Rockwell">(HORSE NEIGHING)</font>

40:53.538 --> 40:56.472
<font face="Rockwell">(HORSE NEIGHS, SNORTS)</font>

41:09.654 --> 41:11.654
<font face="Rockwell">(HORSE NEIGHING)</font>

41:12.791 --> 41:15.625
<font face="Rockwell">(HORSE NEIGHS WEAKLY)</font>

41:17.762 --> 41:19.662
<font face="Rockwell">(LOUD BREATHING)</font>

41:20.732 --> 41:23.499
<font face="Rockwell">(LOUD BREATHING)</font>

41:23.501 --> 41:26.502
<font face="Rockwell">(MUFFLED NEIGHING)</font>

41:34.987 --> 41:37.081
I need to speak to Ms. Venable.

41:37.084 --> 41:40.450
<font face="Rockwell">MEAD:</font> Yes, sir, Mr. Langdon.

41:40.452 --> 41:42.787
Tend to the animals.

41:44.689 --> 41:47.557
<font face="Rockwell">(♫ INTRO TO "TONIGHT YOU
BELONG TO ME" PLAYING ♫)</font>

41:47.559 --> 41:50.065
- <font face="Rockwell"> <i>♫ I know ♫</i> </font>
- <font face="Rockwell"> <i>♫ <i>I know</i> ♫</i> </font>

41:50.068 --> 41:52.462
<font face="Rockwell"> <i>♫ You belong ♫</i> </font>

41:52.464 --> 41:55.732
- <font face="Rockwell"> <i>♫ To somebody new... ♫</i> </font>
- <font face="Rockwell">(HORSE EXHALES)</font>

41:55.734 --> 41:57.068
<font face="Rockwell">(DOOR CLACKS OPEN)</font>

41:57.071 --> 42:03.334
<font face="Rockwell"> <i>♫ But tonight you belong to me... ♫</i> </font>

42:06.764 --> 42:08.544
Wilhemina Venable.

42:08.546 --> 42:10.713
I'm in charge here.

42:10.715 --> 42:13.549
Of course you are.

42:13.551 --> 42:15.684
You don't sound like you believe me.

42:15.687 --> 42:17.720
<font face="Rockwell"> <i>♫ You belong ♫</i> </font>

42:17.722 --> 42:20.690
- Why wouldn't I?
- <font face="Rockwell"> <i>♫ To me... ♫</i> </font>

42:20.692 --> 42:23.526
Seems like you've done a wonderful job.

42:23.528 --> 42:25.896
<i>The walls are still standing.</i>

42:25.899 --> 42:28.175
<i>Your people are alive and healthy.</i>

42:28.178 --> 42:30.975
- <font face="Rockwell">(HORSE SPUTTERS)</font>
<i>- Which is...</i>

42:30.978 --> 42:32.745
<i>- quite a feat...</i>
- <font face="Rockwell">(GUN CHAMBER CLICKS)</font>

42:32.748 --> 42:34.637
- <font face="Rockwell">(HORSE NEIGHS)</font>
<i>- ...considering.</i>

42:34.639 --> 42:37.034
- <font face="Rockwell">(GUNSHOT)</font>
- <font face="Rockwell">(THUDS)</font>

42:37.037 --> 42:38.641
Considering?

42:38.643 --> 42:40.901
That three more Outposts
have been overrun,

42:40.904 --> 42:43.379
and the remaining three
won't last through the year.

42:43.381 --> 42:44.986
Why are you here?

42:44.989 --> 42:46.722
- <font face="Rockwell">(HORSE NEIGHING)</font>
- <font face="Rockwell">(GUNSHOT)</font>

42:46.725 --> 42:49.018
Because it's only a matter of time

42:49.021 --> 42:52.522
before the same thing happens to you.

42:52.524 --> 42:55.792
The good news is,
there's another facility,

42:55.794 --> 42:58.428
a sanctuary.

42:58.430 --> 42:59.940
This one's completely impregnable

42:59.943 --> 43:02.726
and stocked with enough
supplies to last a decade.

43:02.729 --> 43:04.729
You're here to take us there.

43:04.732 --> 43:06.350
<font face="Rockwell">LANGDON:</font> Hmm.

43:06.353 --> 43:08.570
I've been assigned to
evaluate the people here

43:08.573 --> 43:12.115
and select the ones
most worthy of survival.

43:12.118 --> 43:14.972
<i>I could take all of you... or none of you.</i>

43:14.975 --> 43:17.580
- <font face="Rockwell">(RUSTLING BELOW)</font>
<i>- Those who make it live.</i>

43:17.582 --> 43:19.549
- <font face="Rockwell">(LOUD GRUNT)</font>
<i>- Those who don't...</i>

43:24.322 --> 43:26.526
...end up like my horses.

43:26.529 --> 43:28.670
<font face="Rockwell"> <i>♫ Just to little old me. ♫</i> </font>

